e Li-content, the spacing of the oxygen layers and the interlayer cationic disorder. [ 5 ] Cationic reloca-tion [ 6 ] and irreversible order–disorder transitions [ 7,8 ] often occur in layered oxides upon cycling. The near complete Li + extrac-tion from the ordered sites/layers is concomitant with a large lattice volume change, [ 2 ] phase transition, [ 9 ] and even crystal structure collapse. [ 10 ] It is desirable to develop new intercalation materials with better structural tolerance for Li + uptake/release and meanwhile enhanced lithium storage capability. Disordered},
